Job Details
Job Description
The Personal Assistant is responsible for providing secretarial, clerical and administrative support to the Managing Director/Owner to ensure that the work is provided in an effective and efficient manner. The PA is required to exercise independent judgment, technical knowledge of the Managing Director/Owner’s area of responsibilities.
• Perform a wide variety of executive secretarial and administrative duties as required by daily operations in the MD/Owner’s office;
• Answer, screen and accept communication on behalf of the Managing Director/Owner, including telephone calls, e-mail messages, and office visitors; provide assistance using independent judgment to determine those requiring priority attention;
• Attend Managing Director/ Owner’s meeting and take minutes when required;
• Coordinate and maintain Managing Director/ Owner’s activities, schedules, and calendar;
• Make travel arrangements for the Managing Director/Owner's; coordinate with the travel coordinator on this responsibility;
• Develop and recommend office procedures and systems that will ensure smooth office operations;
• Review and summarize miscellaneous reports and documents and prepare background documents as necessary; • Other duties as assigned.
Requirements
Skills 2-5 years office administration and supervision experience; knowledge of MS Office (word, power point, excel) Fluent in English and Arabic.
